HEADWORD: Revisal
<hw>Re*vis"al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Revise</er>.]</ety> <def>The act of revising, or reviewing and
reexamining for correction and improvement; revision; <as>as, the
<ex>revisal</ex> of a manuscript; the <ex>revisal</ex> of a proof sheet;
the <ex>revisal</ex> of a treaty.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Revise</ent>⟦br⟧
